The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Saturday, July 31, 2004 				 IOC profit jumps 56% to Rs 1472cr
 OUR BUREAUX																								July 30: Indian Oil Corporation (IOC) has registered a 56 per cent jump in net profit to touch the Rs 1,472-crore mark in the first quarter of the current financial year compared with Rs 944.67 crore posted in the same period last year. 																								Chairman M. S. Ramachandran attributed the corporations improved performance in the first quarter to higher gross refining margins, which more than doubled from $3.19 per barrel to $6.87 per barrel on a quarter-to-quarter basis.																								Sales turnover went up by 15.2 per cent to Rs 35,577 crore from Rs 30,874 crore in the same quarter of 2003-04. Earnings per share also increased to Rs 12.60 from Rs 8.09 last year.VSNL net zooms 93%																								Videsh Sanchar Nigam has posted a 92.7 per cent rise in first-quarter net profit at Rs 126.8 crore compared with Rs 65.8 crore in the year-ago period. 																								The bottomline went up after it received Rs 46.9 crore as part of a settlement during the quarter. 
